            ANNOUNCING: THE MULTI-LEVEL MARKETING (MLM) ECHO

     We have started a new echo called MLM, the echo for those
     involved or interested in Multi-Level Marketing (sometimes also
     known as "network marketing").  For those of you who are not
     familiar with the phrase "Multi-Level Marketing", this is the
     method by which a large number of products and services are
     sold nowadays.  Some of the better-known firms in this field
     are Amway (home care and other products), and A.J. Williams
     (insurance), but there are literally hundreds of firms that
     utilize this method of marketing their products.

     The need for this echo arose from the fact that messages
     relating to Multi-Level Marketing were appearing with
     increasing frequency in echoes such as FOR-SALE and JOBS.  The
     moderators of such echoes consider MLM discussions as
     "off-topic" and therefore, it is difficult to have a discussion
     about the real benefits or the pitfalls of any such plans.  The
     MLM echo is being introduced to provide a place where such
     discussions will be "on-topic."

     We expect that those who particiapte in the MLM echo will agree
     that Multi-Level Marketing is a valid and responsible method of
     marketing products.  HOWEVER, we also recognize that there are
     irresponsible people who try to use MLM as a "cover" for
     illegal pyramid schemes, but that does not detract from the
     fact that MLM itself is a very valid method of selling products
     or services direct to the customer, that has been utilized for
     years.  Those who disagree, or who feel that _all_ MLM activity
     is a scam of some type, should not be participating in this
     echo.

     The main purpose of this conference is for those engaged in
     Multi-Level Marketing (MLM), or those interested in MLM, to
     discuss various tips, techniques, methods, warnings, legal
     matters, and other information of general interest to those
     engaged in MLM.  Obviously, this will also be a place where
     some of the scams and less-than-honorable operations will also
     be exposed, though the primary purpose of this echo is not to
     "bash" competitive products or services.

     All participants in this conference will be expected to conduct
     themselves in a professional manner.  If you read (or
     participate in) other Fidonet echomail conferences, you may
     have the idea that it's okay to flame people or otherwise act
     like a jerk.  That is definitely NOT the case in this echo.
     Participants are encouraged to read the rules of the echo
     (which will be made available for file request on 1:154/9 under
     the filename "MLM.RUL") before linking in.  We really want to
     try and keep this a high-quality echo that is worth reading
     (particularly since "time is money" to those involved in MLM).

